entry.title: WEATHER ADVISORY , Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 7:12 PM EST Tuesday 27 December 2022

entry.title: Tuesday night: Snow at times heavy. Temperature rising to minus 1 by morning.
entry.summary: Snow at times heavy. Amount 10 to 15 cm. Wind southwest 30 km/h gusting to 50. Temperature rising to minus 1 by morning. Wind chill near minus 11. Forecast issued 7:43 PM EST Tuesday 27 December 2022

entry.title: Wednesday: Periods of snow mixed with ice pellets. High plus 3.
entry.summary: Periods of snow mixed with ice pellets ending early in the afternoon then cloudy with 30 percent chance of flurries or ice pellets. Risk of freezing rain in the morning and afternoon. Local snow and ice pellet amount 2 to 4 cm. Wind southwest 30 km/h. High plus 3. Wind chill minus 8 in the morning. UV index 1 or low. Forecast issued 7:43 PM EST Tuesday 27 December 2022

entry.title: Wednesday night: Chance of flurries. Temperature steady near plus 3. POP 40%
entry.summary: Mainly cloudy with 40 percent chance of flurries or drizzle. Risk of freezing drizzle early in the evening. Wind south 20 km/h gusting to 40 becoming light overnight. Temperature steady near plus 3. Forecast issued 7:43 PM EST Tuesday 27 December 2022
